So, the four squares (1,2), (2,1), (2,3), (3,2) form a valid hitting set. Therefore, four is sufficient. But is three possible? Let's try to find a three-square hitting set. Let's suppose we guess (1,1), (2,2), (3,3). Let's check all rectangles. Horizontal in first row: (1,1) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in second row: (2,2) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in third row: (3,3) isn't adjacent. So, horizontal in third row isn't covered. Vertical in first column: (1,1) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in second column: (2,2) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in third column: (3,3) is guessed. Covered. But horizontal in third row: (3,1) and (3,2) aren't guessed. So, not covered. Therefore, this set fails. Another three-square set: (1,2), (2,1), (2,3). Let's check. Horizontal in first row: (1,1) and (1,2). (1,2) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in second row: (2,1) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in third row: (3,1) and (3,2). Not guessed. Not covered. Vertical in first column: (1,1) and (2,1). (2,1) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in second column: (2,1) and (2,2). (2,1) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in third column: (2,3) and (3,3). (3,3) not guessed. Not covered. So, horizontal in third row and vertical in third column aren't covered. Therefore, this set fails. Another three-square set: (1,1), (2,2), (3,1). Let's check. Horizontal in first row: (1,1) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in second row: (2,2) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in third row: (3,1) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in first column: (1,1) and (2,1). (2,1) not guessed. Not covered. Vertical in second column: (2,2) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in third column: (2,3) and (3,3). Not guessed. Not covered. So, vertical in first column and third column aren't covered. Fails. Another three-square set: (1,1), (1,2), (2,2). Let's check. Horizontal in first row: (1,1) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in second row: (2,2) is guessed. Covered. Horizontal in third row: (3,1) and (3,2). Not guessed. Not covered. Vertical in first column: (1,1) and (2,1). (2,1) not guessed. Not covered. Vertical in second column: (1,2) and (2,2). (2,2) is guessed. Covered. Vertical in third column: (2,3) and (3,3).
